headline: Morgan Stanley Infra Partners eyes $2 billion Permian pipelines sale, sources say
summary: (Reuters) -Morgan Stanley Infrastructure Partners is exploring the sale of its majority stake in Brazos Midstream II, with a deal expected to value its holding at more than $2 billion including debt, three people familiar with the matter said.  The company also owns associated infrastructure including natural gas compression capabilities and crude storage.  Investment bankers at Jefferies Financial Group in recent weeks have been shopping MSIP's controlling stake in Brazos to potential buyers, including midstream companies and investment firms, the people said, asking not to be identified because the discussions are private.
